  "color_desc": {
    "kicker": "The color · in plain words",
    "title_html": "What you're <em>looking</em> at.",
    "prose_paragraphs": [
      "Designers reach for Country Gray when they want a roof that disappears into 'looks correct' rather than competing for attention. It is balanced, slightly cool, and difficult to pair badly. On a Florida house with bright sun and white stucco, it is one of the safest specifications you can write.",
      "CertainTeed uses a tight blend of dark gray and faint blue-gray granules to keep the surface visually alive. The result is a roof that reads as a clean architectural line from the street and a textured surface up close.",
      "Pairs cleanly with white, cream, navy, sage, and warm terra-cotta sidings. Almost any house color works underneath it."
    ],
